manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: AMD Radeon RX 550 4GB GDDR5 Video Graphics Card for PC Gaming Features 4GB of GDDR5 memory, boost clock up to 1180 MHz512 stream processor high-specification chips, even compatible with ITX chassisDP/HDMI/DVI-D three interfaces, supports Blu-ray HD, 4K@60Hz outputIt is an ideal platform for building a Home Theater PC (HTPC), including support for HDMI 4K60, 4K video playback, HEVC content, HDR, FreeSync 2, and more.As well as GPU acceleration of some application software, such as Photoshop, Premier and so on. Attentions:If it's no video signal when plugged in the gpu into the PCIe slot, and not sure if pc is compatible, please try to update the drivers via AMD website.

Polaris Architecture Polaris architecture precisely combines the latest 14nm FinFET process with AMD's advanced power management, gating and clocking technologies for a super cool, quiet gaming experience. Silent Cooling Fan This RX550 fits the system perfectly, is very quiet.Equipped with independent cooling fan,which keep the GPU cooler and running stronger to keep lower working temperature and higher efficiency, it also can drives 4k monitor, making your daily work smooth and fast. Multiple Interfaces Equipped with DVI, DP and HDMI ports,multi simultaneous display capable.Support Blu-ray HD, 60Hz output 4K resolution.Light gaming is probably ok,it's just great to show a lot of working windows.

FPS performance on mainstream games The Radeon RX 550 is capable of handling most everyday applications, including browsing the web, editing photo videos, watching HD and 4K videos, and even playing some games at 1080P. Also runs some common software, such as Adobe's Photoshop and Premiere. High heat dissipation performance The low-power RX 550 combined with the Chill On energy-saving cooling program not only makes your keyboard and mouse response time faster by 41%, but also saves 37% of GPU power consumption, and reduces heat dissipation by 15 degrees. Smooth gameplay The Radeon RX 550 can perfectly support 4K resolution 60 frame picture output, HEVC 4K video codec and HDR format content output. Online games are the basic needs of most notebook users now. And the Radeon RX 550 also has a pretty good 4K video and low-power experience.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pretty much the best you can get for the older Dell Optiplex models.
reviews.reviewText: As mentioned above, while this card is a bit old, it's the best option for upgrading many small form factor desktops. This card supports up to 3 monitors (the VGA port needs to use a second slot for SFF desktops).In my case, the second slot on my PC was used for a dual M.2 card, but I cheated and purchased a different bracket and connected that to the M.2 card, cut a space for the VGA port and can now run all 3 displays at the same time. Actually, I also use the 3 additional video ports on the motherboard and can (and have) run 6 monitors at the same time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars This graphics card caused numerous crashes and freezes in Windows 10. Card confirmed as the cause.
reviews.reviewText: I purchased the QTHREE AMD Radeon RX 550 Graphics Card on 9/28/2023 for a new computer I built from scratch (Windows 10, i5-13600K, 32GB Corsair RAM, ASUS Prime B660-PLUS D4 motherboard, etc). I have a lot of experience building PCs from scratch.For the next 2 months, I suffered lock-ups, screen freezes, resets, Windows WHEA errors, etc. After checking everything, driver updates, bios, windows updates, and more I was finally able to narrow the problem down to the QTHREE AMD Radeon RX 550 Graphics Card.In late November, I replaced it with an ASUS GeForce GT 1030 2GB GDDR5 HDMI DVI Graphics Card and the problems all went away. I've been holding off writing this review until I was 100%. I am.

reviews.reviewTitle: Carte Graphique utiliser sur un poste DELL Optiplex 9010 MT WIN11PRO
reviews.reviewText: Je souhaiter optimiser mon poste DELL OPT 9010MT sous WIN11PRO.ayant envie de tester sa capacité à jouer à certain jeux et de l'utiliser en médiacenter pour de la 4K ou 1080P.La possibilité d'utiliser 2 ou 3 écrans c'est l'idéal lors d'un jeux ou de la bureautique.La carte graphique s'installe facilement se renseigné avant d'acheter pour éviter qu'elle ne rentre pas dans un SFF par exemple mon autre DELL OPT 3040 un peux plus récent pour de la bureautique etc.Le prix est abordable pour rendre une deuxième vie à un pc.Pas besoins d'installer de pilote qui s'installe automatiquement si vous possédez une connexion internet pour ma part j'ai attendu qu'elle que minute et tout c'est installer grâce à la fibre est le pc connecter en RJ45.
